  "prompt": "What is the best smartphone to date?",
  "response": "As of my last update in April 2023, the best smartphone can vary based on individual needs such as camera quality, battery life, performance, and price. However, some of the top-rated smartphones at that time were:\n\n1. **Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra** - Known for its high-end specifications, including a versatile camera system with a 200MP main sensor, a large vibrant display, and powerful performance with the Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 processor.\n\n2. **iPhone 14 Pro Max** - Praised for its excellent performance with the A16 Bionic chip, advanced camera system with a 48MP main sensor, and the new Dynamic Island feature, making it a top choice for iOS users.\n\n3. **Google Pixel 7 Pro** - Highly regarded for its camera capabilities and clean, feature-rich Android software experience, along with solid performance and a good balance of features.\n\n4. **OnePlus 11** - Offers flagship-level performance at a slightly lower price point than some competitors, with fast charging and a high-quality display.\n\nWhen choosing the best smartphone, consider what features are most important to you, such as camera quality, battery life, software ecosystem (iOS vs. Android), and budget. It's also a good idea to check the latest reviews and possibly wait for upcoming releases if you're not in immediate need of a new phone.",
